\pard\f0\fs28 Herbs or shrubs. Verticillasters few- to many-flowered, crowded or distant. Calyx tubular, 5- to 10-veined, 5-toothed. Corolla 2-lipped; upper lip hooded, emarginate; lower lip patent, 3-lobed. Stamens included or exserted; anther cells divergent. Style-branches unequal. Nutlets trigonous, glabrous or pubescent.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  Most species occur on dry, rocky ground.
\par

\par

