\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b pungens}  (Willd.) Maire ex DeFilipps, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  64}: 233 (1971) ({\i P. pungens} Willd.): Stem whitish, stellate tomentose, the hairs up to 0·1 mm, sometimes with a secondary indumentum of hairs up to 1 mm, rarely glabrous. Cauline leaves 7-13 cm, lanceolate, cuneate at base, entire, remotely denticulate or serrate, stellate-puberulent or stellate-hispidulous above. Verticillasters 2- to 6-(10-)flowered.{\i  S.E. Europe, extending locally westwards to Spain and northwards to} c. 53°{\i  N. in C. Russia}.
\par

